    "body": "I was able to retrofit starship's support for pyenv for uv (not that I don't really activate venvs):\r\n\r\n```toml\r\n# ~/.config/starship.toml\r\n[python]\r\npyenv_version_name = true\r\npyenv_prefix = \"uv \"\r\n```\r\n\r\nThen make an alias for `pyenv version-name`:\r\n\r\n```sh\r\npyenv() {\r\n    if [ \"$1\" = \"version-name\" ]; then\r\n        uv run python --version | sed 's/Python //g'\r\n    else\r\n        echo \"pyenv: command not found\"\r\n    fi\r\n}\r\n```",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "pin": null,
    "reactions": {
