    "updated_at": "2025-04-11T08:42:27Z",
    "body": "Currently you can add something like:\n```toml\npython_binary = [[\"uv\", \"run\", \"--no-python-downloads\", \"python\"]]\n```\n`python_binary` can take a list of either strings or other lists of strings. After https://github.com/starship/starship/pull/6523 landed to add this, it became known that `pyenv.cfg` also seems to house relevant info, and that wouldn't need to execute a binary. The worry is that there could be an untrusted python binary that would get executed just upon entering the directory (if .venv was checked in, though really you should never clone a repo that has done this). The binary config change was chosen as it also supports poetry display.\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "pin": null,
