    "body": "Thanks! `python_binary = [[...]]` doesn't work like that, it will just try to run each of these commands, in your case it works because \"python\" is the last command.\n\nThe untrusted binary is a fair point. There is now also a dedicated `uv python find --only-version`, but I think internally it might also execute the potentially untrusted python binary. https://github.com/astral-sh/uv/pull/12376",
