    "body": "> Thanks! python_binary = [[...]] doesn't work like that, it will just try to run each of these commands, in your case it works because \"python\" is the last command.\n\n#6523 should have implemented this to work. So you could have `[[\"uv\", \"run\", \"--no-python-downloads\", \"python\"], \"python\", \"python 3\", python 2]` and this would run `uv run --no-python-downloads python (--version)` first, and then try the rest after.\n\nhttps://github.com/starship/starship/blob/6988b6b1e1d894583f0088e010a0f031c45545b2/src/modules/python.rs#L95-L114",
