    "body": "> Looks like its still working for me just fine\n> \n> ![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/7c9ab417-44cd-4e2d-8c68-6dd6dbe7e709)\n> \n> my config:\n> \n> [python]\n> python_binary = [[\"uv\", \"run\", \"--no-python-downloads\", \"python\"]]\n\nI really like your solution. It's the simplest one. I'd recommend adding `--no-project` argument to uv here. Without it uv creates uv.lock files in every catalog where python is detected, even when it's not a UV managed project.",
