    "updated_at": "2026-03-08T00:28:45Z",
    "body": "It's my workaround that allows switching between uv and a regular venv, with different colors to tell them apart.\n\n```toml\nright_format = \"\"\"\n${custom.python_fallback}\\\n${custom.uv}\\\n$time\n\"\"\"\n\n[custom.uv]\ndetect_files = ['uv.lock']\nsymbol = \"\\ue73c \"\ncommand = 'uv run python --version'\nformat = '[uv $symbol$output ]($style)'\nstyle = \"bold #22C55E\"\n\n[custom.python_fallback]\ndetect_extensions = ['py']\ndetect_files = ['pyproject.toml', 'requirements.txt', '!uv.lock']\nsymbol = \"\\ue73c \"\ncommand = 'python --version'\nformat = '[via ](white)[$symbol$output]($style) '\nstyle = \"bold yellow\"\n```",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "pin": null,
